2 December 2019 - Defence advocate Vernon Jantjies died in a hail of bullets at a petrol station in Lentegeur on Sunday night, in front of his daughter and onlookers. 2 December 2019 - Minister of Public Works and Infrastructure Patricia de Lille will host a fund raising golf day for victims of gender based violence. 2 December 2019 - Minister Fikile Mbalula and the Metro Police in Johannesburg launched their festive season campaign effort to nab drunk drivers and reduce road carnage. 2 December 2019 - Dudu Myeni is back in court Monday as SAA’s future is still unclear.